<br>

<h2>
How to get started in . . .
</h2>

<center>

<H1>Post & Riposte</H1>
<h2><I>The Atlantic Monthly</I> 's <br>
 Web Conferencing System</h2>

</center>
<br>

<blockquote>

<h3>New Members</h3>

When you enter Post & Riposte for the first time, an authentication window
will pop up, asking you to enter your USERNAME and PASSWORD. Since you are a new
user, you will not yet have chosen these labels. <p>

<ul>
<li>Take a second to choose a USERNAME and a PASSWORD.  For security 
reasons, we suggest that you <b>not</b> use your real name as your 
USERNAME, but you are free to do as you wish.<p>  

<li>Upon entering your USERNAME 
and PASSWORD you will be asked if you would like to register as a New 
Member.  Click on the button that says, <B>"Yes, I am entering as a new 
user."</B> <p>

<li>You will then be prompted to fill out a registration form.  At this time, 
you may change the USERNAME and PASSWORD that you initially chose.  Please 
note: although you may later change the information on the registration 
form, including your password, this will be your LAST opportunity to change 
your USERNAME.<p>
</ul>

Got that? (We've tried to make it as confusing as possible.) <B>Okay then --  <A 
HREF="http://gtwy.theatlantic.com/webboard/$webb.exe/~115/">enter here</B></A>.<p>

<br>


<h3>Current Members</h3>

All you need do once you are a registered member is enter your USERNAME and 
PASSWORD each time.  You will only be asked for this information once per 
session. If you forget your USERNAME or PASSWORD, please email <A 
HREF="mailto:web@theatlantic.com">web@theatlantic.com</A> for assistance.<p>

Registered members 
<A 
HREF="http://gtwy.theatlantic.com/webboard/$webb.exe/~115/">enter here.</A><p>
<br>

</blockquote>

<font size=1>
Copyright &copy; 1996 by The Atlantic Monthly Company.  All rights reserved.
