<li><A HREF="/atlantic/atlweb/poetry/antholog/aaindx.htm">An Audible Anthology</A>.  Poets read their work from <I>The Atlantic</I>'s pages.<p>

<li><A HREF="/atlantic/atlweb/poetry/atlpoets/poetindx.htm">More <i>Atlantic Monthly</i> Poetry Online</A>. Poems published in the magazine since November, 1993.<p>

<li><B>Special features:</B><p>
<ul>
<li> <A HREF="/atlantic/atlweb/poetry/poetint.htm">The Matter of Poetry</A><p>

<li> <A HREF="/atlantic/atlweb/poetry/Frost/FrostInt.htm">Robert Frost in <i>The Atlantic Monthly</I>: The First Three Poems and One That Got Away</A><p>

<li> <A HREF="/atlantic/atlweb/aandc/Dante/danthome.htm">The Deep Passage: Dante, Longfellow, and Pinsky</A><p>

<li> <A HREF="/atlantic/atlweb/poetry/EmilyD/EDintro.htm">Emily Dickinson (Un)discovered</A><p>

<li> <A HREF="/atlantic/atlweb/poetry/Whitman/Walt.htm">"Reminiscences of Walt Whitman"</A> (1902)<p>

<li> <A HREF="/atlantic/atlweb/poetry/nov1857/nov1857.htm">Volume One, Number One -- November, 1857</A><p><br>
</font>
</ul>
</ul>
<li> <A HREF="/atlantic/atlweb/wordgame/current.htm"><B>Word Games</B></A><BR> <font size=3>Hosted by Emily Cox and Henry Rathvon, creators of the Atlantic Puzzler.<p></font>
</font>
</ul>

<br>

<li> <A HREF="/atlantic/about/aboutf.htm"><B>About <i>The Atlantic</I></B></A><p>

