recognizing that the American people are quite capable of 
thinking for themselves about the issues that concern them 
without massive parental support from the experts in 
Washington and the media.  I applaud your effort at bringing 
more common opinions into the discussion about issues that 
affect the everyday person. The American democracy was 
founded on freedoms, and information is the cheapest of them 
all. Give the people the information they need to make an 
intelligent decision, and the government will be surprised at 
the outcome. Congratulations on leading the charge. <P>

