<TITLE>
TransAtlantic
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=ffffff>
<center>
	<a href="../images/headbar.map"><img src="../images/headbar.gif" ISMAP 
width=480 height=100 border=0 alt="The Atlantic Monthly"></a>
</center>

<pre>
</pre>

<CENTER>

<h1>TransAtlantic</h1>
<h3>Your Guide to What's New in<br> <I>The Atlantic Monthly </I> on the Web</h3><p>

</CENTER>
<pre>
</pre>

<blockquote>

TransAtlantic is a free e-mail newsletter, updating subscribers on what's 
new in <i>The Atlantic Monthly</i>'s digital edition.  TransAtlantic is 
short yet comprehensive, informal yet informative.  It comes out 
approximately once a week.<p>

Once you've subscribed, you can remove your name from the mailing list at 
any time. The e-mail addresses of TransAtlantic subscribers are NOT 
available to anyone outside of the magazine.<p>

To subscribe to TransAtlantic, enter your e-mail address in the box below, 
then click "Send."  If you are already receiving TransAtlantic, and would 
like to be removed from the list, click the "Unsubscribe" box.<p>

</blockquote>

<Form Method="POST" 
Action="http://www3.theatlantic.com/cgi-bin/tasub.cgi">

<blockquote>

	<input name="mlfrom" size="40"><p>
	<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="usub" VALUE="usub">Unsubscribe from
	TransAtlantic.<p>
	
	<input type=submit value="Send">
	<input type=reset value="Clear">	
</form>

<p>

If your browser does not support forms, please send mail to <a 
href="mailto:transatl@theatlantic.com">TransAtl@TheAtlantic.com</a> with 
the words "Join TransAtlantic" in the message body.  (Subject lines will 
be ignored.)<p>
<br>
</blockquote>
<hr>
</font>
<font size=1>
Copyright &copy; 1996 The Atlantic Monthly.  All rights reserved.
</font>
<p>

