<html>
<head>
<title>Arts, Culture & Comment Index</title>

<meta=atlantic unbound magazine arts culture commentary essay entertainment  
literature politics society poetry>

</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff">

<!-- HEADER GRAPHIC -->
<center>
<a href="../images/headau.map">
<img src="../images/headau.gif" ISMAP width=480 height=100 border=0
alt="Atlantic Unbound"></a><p>
</center>

<br>

<a name="arts">


<H2>Arts, Culture & Comment -- <font size=4><I>Index</I></font></H2>


<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=0 VALIGN=CENTER CELLPADDING=15>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=50% VALIGN=TOP>






<b><A HREF="./digicult/dcindex.htm">Digital Culture</A></B><br>
A new monthly column by Ralph Lombreglia considers the present state and possible future of arts and letters in the digital realm. Plus, an excerpt from Lombreglia's essay in <I>Tolstoy's Dictaphone: Technology and the Muse</I>; an exchange with Sven Birkerts, author of <I>The Gutenberg Elegies</I>; Robert Pinsky on poetry, computers, and translating Dante; and more. <p>

<b><A Href="./jazz/bebop.htm">Jazz in the '90s: Bebop and 
Beyond?</b></A><br>A look at jazz in the '90s -- its influences, rising 
stars, and prospects for the future.  Read an interview with jazz critic 
Francis Davis, author of <I>Bebop and Nothingness: Jazz and Pop at the End 
of the Century</I>, and peruse <I>Atlantic</I> articles on jazz from as far 
back as 1922.<p>	



<b><A Href="./aandc/movies/movhome.htm">The Decline of Film?</a></b><br>
Movie critics Pauline Kael and Michael Sragow comment on the state of the art.<p>

<b><A Href="./aandc/gardens/gardhome.htm">A Century of Gardens</a></b><br> Four 
articles from different time periods discuss the pleasures of gardens and 
gardening.<br>


</TD>
<TD WIDTH=50% VALIGN=TOP>


<b><a href= "../ae/96dec/96dec.htm">Arts & Entertainment 
Preview</a></b><br> <i>Sponsored by The Chrysler Corporation and its 
divisions.</i><br>A critical guide to cultural happenings, covering what's 
new and noteworthy in jazz, popular music, dance, theater, classical music, 
and film.<p>
	
<b><a href="./corby/cklist.htm">Food: Corby's Table</a></b><br>
<i>Atlantic</i> senior editor Corby Kummer treats us to favorite 
recipes from his favorite chefs.<p>

	
<b><a href="./jack/jblist.htm">Jack Beatty</a></b><br> A 
compilation of book reviews, political 
commentary, and more, by <I>Atlantic</I> senior editor Jack Beatty.  <p>


<b><A Href="./jf-npr/JFlist.htm">James 
Fallows</a></b><br> A collection of radio commentaries, articles, and 
assorted curiosities by <I>The Atlantic</I>'s eminent computer junkie, 
tennis bum, and contributing editor (now also editor of <A 
HREF="http://www.usnews.com/usnews/">a certain national news 
magazine</A>).<p>

<b><a href="./cullen/cmlist.htm">Still Curious: Cullen Murphy</a></b><br>
How much stuff should we save?  Are Americans getting enough sleep?  What 
is snow?  This collection of recent essays offers a glimpse into the 
inquisitive mind of <i>The Atlantic</i>'s managing editor.<p>



</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

</CENTER>

